# AI DevCamp — core rules

## Next.js

This repo uses **Next.js with breaking changes** vs common training knowledge. Before adding routes, config, or App Router APIs, **consult the in-repo guides** under `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` (and heed deprecations). Do not assume APIs from older Next versions.

## Scope and edits

- **Only change what the task requires.** No drive-by refactors, no unrelated files, no “cleanup” unless asked.
- **Match the codebase:** imports, naming, types, component structure, and Tailwind/Radix patterns used nearby.
- **Reuse and extend** existing helpers (`src/lib/`, `src/components/`, server modules) instead of duplicating logic.
- **Do not remove** unrelated comments or code in passing.

## Documentation

- **Do not add or edit** markdown under `docs/` or README-style files **unless the user explicitly asks** for documentation updates.

## Verification

- After substantive changes, run **`npm run lint`** and **`npm run build`** (from the project root) and fix failures you introduce.
